        GREETINGS_AND_WELCOME_TO_THE_CHOCOBO_RACING_ASSOCIATION                 = 9367,  -- Greetings, and welcome to the Chocobo Racing Association's (CRA) [San d'Oria/Bastok/Windurst] branch. This service area is here to accommodate our more experienced and accomplished racers.
        I_AM_TRULY_SORRY_SIR_MA_AM_BUT                                          = 9368,  -- I am truly sorry sir/ma'am], but we are unable to service your request here. This service area only caters to [San d'Orian/Bastokan/Windurstian] CRA Classic winners.
        REGISTRATION_FOR_SUCH_AN_EVENT_CAN_BE_CARRIED                           = 9369,  -- Registration for such an event can be carried out at the service areas for beginning and intermediate racers. Please speak to the attendants there for further assistance.
        THE_ORGANIZING_ATTENDANTS_IN_EACH_LOCATION_ARE_AS                       = 9370,  -- The organizing attendants in each location are as follows: [Southern San d'Oria: Alangriche/Bastok Mines: Jazgeh/Windurst Waters: Turumi-Byrumi] [Northern San d'Oria: Monteverle/Bastok Markets: Galienne/Windurst Port: Lhimo Keanyohn] [Port San d'Oria: Ramiene/Port Bastok: Salvador/Windurst Woods: Rungaga].
        FOR_BEGINNING_AND_INTERMEDIATE_RACES_YOU_LL_WANT                        = 9371,  -- For beginning and intermediate races, you'll want to speak with [Alangriche/Jazgeh/Rungaga].
        MY_APOLOGIES_SIR_MA_AM_BUT_IT_APPEARS                                   = 9372,  -- My apologies, sir/ma'am], but it appears that you have yet to conduct all of the necessary processing at the service area for beginning and intermediate racers. Please speak to the attendants there for further assistance.
        MY_APOLOGIES_SIR_MA_AM_BUT_IT_APPEARS_2                                 = 9373,  -- My apologies, sir/ma'am], but it appears that you have yet to conduct all of the necessary processing at the service area for advanced and veteran racers. Please speak to the attendants there for further assistance.
        WHICH_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_HEAR_ABOUT_CRA                                  = 9374,  -- Which would you like to hear about? CRA rationale behind veteran races. How do I register for a race? How do I prepare for a race? What are chocobucks? What kinds of races are there? What are racing teams? What about race opponents? Quit. Return.
        WITH_THE_ESTABLISHMENT_OF_THE_CHOCOBO_CIRCUIT_AND                       = 9375,  -- With the establishment of the Chocobo Circuit and the introduction of chocobo races, the hidden talents of a number of chocobos across Vana'diel finally had a venue in which to come to fruition.
        AS_THE_NEXT_STEP_THE_CRA_RECOGNIZED_THESE                               = 9376,  -- As the next step, the CRA recognized these rare and valuable talents, and developed a new, special kind of race to showcase them even more than before!
        THE_MONSTER_RACES                                                       = 9377,  -- The Monster Races!
        WITHOUT_THE_INTERFERENCE_OF_JOCKEYS_BREEDERS_CAN_NOW                    = 9378,  -- Without the interference of jockeys, breeders can now pit their chocobos head-to-head against a number of monster species in brutal, raw, no-holds-barred racing!
        EVEN_SOME_OF_THE_CRA_S_VERY_OWN                                         = 9379,  -- Even some of the CRA's very own best and brightest chocobos will be entering into these races geared specifically to our veteran clientele. What more thrilling way to spend a day at the races than to see Vana'diel's most elite chocobos competing against its most fiendish monsters!?
        FIRST_OF_ALL_YOUR_CHOCOBO_MUST_BE_FULLY_2                               = 9380,  -- First of all, your chocobo must be fully grown. It doesn't matter if you are still tending to it, or if it has been sent to pasture, as long as it is large enough to ride.
        NEXT_YOU_MUST_BRING_ME_EITHER_OR_THIS_2                                 = 9381,  -- Next, you must bring me either % or %. This is all I will require. There are no hidden fees.
        AS_YOUR_CHOCOBO_DEVELOPS_BE_SURE_TO_RE_2                                = 9382,  -- As your chocobo develops, be sure to re-register it. This will ensure that your steed is provided with the equipment that most suits its current condition.
        FINALLY_YOU_MAY_ONLY_REGISTER_ONE_CHOCOBO_AT_2                          = 9383,  -- Finally, you may only register one chocobo at a time, but are free to register a new bird whenever you wish. You need only speak with me to make any necessary changes.
        SINCE_THESE_RACES_ARE_GEARED_TOWARDS_OUR_MORE                           = 9384,  -- Since these races are geared towards our more veteran racers and will not make use of jockeys, all in-race conduct is based solely on the chocobos themselves. The CRA wants these races to be as pure as possible!
        THE_SAME_PHILOSOPHY_APPLIES_TO_THE_USAGE_OF                             = 9385,  -- The same philosophy applies to the usage of items as well. Simply preset the items you wish for your chocobo to have at its disposal. It will use them as it sees fit based on real-time assessment of racing conditions.
        MANY_BREEDERS_ARE_DISTRESSED_BY_THESE_RULES_BUT                         = 9386,  -- Many breeders are distressed by these rules, but we assure you there is no need for concern. If your chocobo has progressed far enough in the Chocobo Circuit to even be participating in the Monster Races, it is a given that it has enough know-how to use its items wisely. Have faith in your bird.
        ALSO_AS_WITH_OTHER_RACES_IN_THE_PAST                                    = 9387,  -- Also, as with other races in the past, you will be able to check on the strengths and weaknesses of your opponents at this service area. Many breeders like to use this information for developing their race strategies, and we encourage you to do the same.
        DEPENDING_ON_YOUR_CHOCOBO_S_PERFORMANCE_IN_SELECT_2                     = 9388,  -- Depending on your chocobo's performance in select CRA-sanctioned races, you may or may not receive a prize consisting of VCS-mint chocobucks.
        CHOCOBUCKS_CAN_BE_USED_TO_PURCHASE_ITEMS_AS_2                           = 9389,  -- Chocobucks can be used to purchase items, as well as upgrade your mount. Chocobucks are also required to participate in official races.
        CURRENTLY_PLAYERS_CAN_EARN_UP_TO_BUT_NO_2                               = 9390,  -- Currently, players can earn up to, but no more than, 1000 chocobucks. However, this may change without notice.
        THERE_ARE_TWO_MAIN_TYPES_OF_RACES_2                                     = 9391,  -- There are two main types of races.
        THE_FIRST_TYPE_IS_CALLED_AN_OFFICIAL_RACE_2                             = 9392,  -- The first type is called an official race. To participate in one of these, you will require chocobucks.
        PLACING_IN_AN_OFFICIAL_RACE_WILL_EARN_YOU_2                             = 9393,  -- Placing in an official race will earn you gil. The more races you complete, the more respected you will become in the breeder community.
        YOU_MAY_ALSO_TAKE_PART_IN_AN_OFFICIAL_2                                 = 9394,  -- You may also take part in an official race as often as needed to complete the specified objectives.
        HOWEVER_AFTER_SOME_OF_THE_MORE_GRUELING_RACES_2                         = 9395,  -- However, after some of the more grueling races, you may be required to wait before entering the next. This is to give your chocobo, as well as the others, an opportunity to rest before running again.
        THE_SECOND_TYPE_OF_RACE_IS_CALLED_A_2                                   = 9396,  -- The second type of race is called a free run. Unlike the official races, these can be run at any time, regardless of the results of a previous match. In addition, you will have the opportunity to earn chocobucks depending on your chocobo's performance.
        YOU_ARE_NOT_ABLE_TO_SIGN_UP_FOR                                         = 9397,  -- You are not able to sign up for free runs at this location. To do so, please visit the appropriate service area for beginning and intermediate racers. Thank you for your understanding.
        THE_CRA_IS_SPLIT_UP_INTO_THREE_RACING_2                                 = 9398,  -- The CRA is split up into three racing teams representing Bastok, Windurst, and San d'Oria.
        EACH_TEAM_HAS_ITS_OWN_SKILLED_JOCKEYS_AND_2                             = 9399,  -- Each team has its own skilled jockeys, and offers unique services that cannot be obtained at the other two.
        BREEDERS_ARE_ALLOWED_TO_REGISTER_WITH_ANY_TEAM_2                        = 9400,  -- Breeders are allowed to register with any team they like, and may change their affiliation at any time.
        IN_THE_EVENT_THAT_YOU_WISH_TO_LEAVE_2                                   = 9401,  -- In the event that you wish to leave a racing team, all official race results, as well as earned chocobucks, will be saved.
        YOU_NEVER_HAVE_TO_WORRY_THAT_YOUR_PAST_2                                = 9402,  -- You never have to worry that your past accomplishments may be deleted and lost forever. You only need rejoin the team to restore all your old data.
        ANYWAY_THERE_IS_NO_HARM_IN_VISITING_ALL_2                               = 9403,  -- Anyway, there is no harm in visiting all three racing teams to find which one suits you best (though I know you'll choose this one).
        YOUR_OPPONENTS_IN_THE_OFFICIAL_MONSTER_RACES_WILL                       = 9404,  -- Your opponents in the official monster races will be any of a host of beasts reared and trained by racing aficionado and announcer extraordinaire, Markovich.
        WE_ENSURE_ALL_PARTICIPATING_BREEDERS_THAT_THESE_MONSTERS                = 9405,  -- We ensure all participating breeders that these monsters are in no way enhanced or engineered for racing excellence. The CRA has been adamant about maintaining race participants to as close to their natural state of being as possible.
        THOUGH_EACH_VARIETY_OF_MONSTER_DOES_IN_FACT                             = 9406,  -- Though each variety of monster does in fact possess characteristic abilities and traits. And they have undergone extensive training to optimize their use of these in races.
        AS_WITH_THE_CHOCOBOS_HOWEVER_THE_MONSTERS_WILL                          = 9407,  -- As with the chocobos, however, the monsters will be absent jockeys of any kind. It is possible, and expected, that they will often unleash their wild, animalistic instincts on the racetrack. Consider yourself warned.
        IN_THE_SPIRIT_OF_DRAWING_CROWDS_THE_CRA                                 = 9408,  -- In the spirit of drawing crowds, the CRA has also elected to place some of their finest birds on the racing roster as well. Breeders can also expect to see other superior-class chocobos taking part. It's going to take a lot more than just speed and endurance to win these races!
        FINALLY_IN_THE_ABSENCE_OF_JOCKEYS_FINISH_LINE                           = 9409,  -- Finally, in the absence of jockeys, finish-line sensors will be employed. These devices will be attached to the contestants' ankles, or in the absence of ankles, some other such appropriate place.
        UELER_S_RACEPARTICIPANTS_2_OBJECTIVE_PLACE_1ST                          = 9410,  -- ueler's RaceParticipants: 2 Objective: Place 1st
        AND_NOW_MARKOVICH_S_UNDENIABLY_UNORTHODOX_AND_ARGUABLY                  = 9411,  -- And now, Markovich's undeniably unorthodox, and arguably downright unethical, monster race is about to begin!
        URVIVAL_RACEPARTICIPANTS_8_OBJECTIVE_PLACE_1ST                          = 9412,  -- urvival RaceParticipants: 8 Objective: Place 1st
        FOLLOWING_SUCH_A_FINE_SHOWING_IN_THE_DUELER                             = 9413,  -- Following such a fine showing in the Dueler's Race, the next contest is about to start! Who will be the last beast standing?
        EADLY_RACEPARTICIPANTS_8_OBJECTIVE_PLACE_1ST                            = 9414,  -- eadly RaceParticipants: 8 Objective: Place 1st
        WARNING_THE_NEXT_RACE_CONTAINS_MONSTERS_OF_UNPRECEDENTED                = 9415,  -- Warning! The next race contains monsters of unprecedented nastiness. Enter at your own risk! The name says it all!
        YSTERY_RACEPARTICIPANTS_4_CHOCOBOS_4_OBJECTIVE_PLACE_1ST                = 9416,  -- ystery RaceParticipants: 4 chocobos & 4 ??? Objective: Place 1st
        WHAT_S_THIS_WE_VE_BEEN_ASKED_TO                                         = 9417,  -- What's this? We've been asked to pass along yet another challenge, this time from an anonymous source! I'm not altogether clear on what is about to transpire...
        ETHAL_RACEPARTICIPANTS_8_OBJECTIVE_PLACE_1ST                            = 9418,  -- ethal RaceParticipants: 8 Objective: Place 1st
        THE_GAMES_ARE_OVER_LADIES_AND_GENTLEMEN_MARKOVICH                       = 9419,  -- The games are over, ladies and gentlemen. Markovich is laying it all on the table. Here come his most ferocious beasts to date!
        REAM_RACEPARTICIPANTS_8_OBJECTIVE_PLACE_1ST                             = 9420,  -- ream RaceParticipants: 8 Objective: Place 1st
        THIS_IS_THE_MOMENT_YOU_VE_ALL_BEEN                                      = 9421,  -- This is the moment you've all been waiting for. The CRA has brought its racing elite out from the stables! The treacherous offroad track is fraught with perils! And an absolutely awe-inspiring trophy is ready for the winner! Bragging rights for life are on the line!
        WHICH_RACE_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_RERUN_DUELER                               = 9422,  -- Which race would you like to rerun? Dueler's Race. Survival Race. Deadly Race. Mystery Race. Lethal Race. Dream Race. ------ ------ Quit. Return.
